I was happy to see a place that was different and familiar to me in the mall. The employees where nice and I was desperate for something that's not typical mall food. I purchased a bowl with skewered chicken, rice, tomato and cucumber chopped salsa, falafel and humus. It was the worst experience ever. The rice was strong it tasted like cinnamon, star anise, nutmeg, curry, and all spice. The chicken skewered was just putred I don't even know how to describe it. The falafel was left out and old. The humus was fluffy and light which I really liked and I liked the tomato and cucumber salsa.  I told the person who was in charge that I was not satisfied and the food was not the way other places I've eaten at similar food restaurants. But he was arguing with me and telling me that that same Saturday 200 people ate from his stop and no one has given any complaints (there is always a first for everything) I highly doubt it, there is always more than a 5% chance of getting a complaint.  To add there where no people there lined up which should have given me the first clue the second clue was the fly I ignored huvering over the food, and third the rice was a bit dry and dis-colored.  I even told the man who was acting like an unprofessional leader or manager that I didn't even ask for my money back and he kept on telling me I was wrong for feeling how I felt (when it's my feelings how are you going to tell me how I feel seriously dude?). My mother had interfere and to take me away and told him it's okay keep the money and take the bad review. He obviously needed the sale more than I needed my $12.  Maybe I had high expectations. I wasn't even rude I kept a pretty good composure the whole time he was insulting me and my intelligence.  The only reason why I gave one star was because the humus was light and fluffy.
